@startuml wifi_state_machine
!theme plain
title Air Quality Node – WiFi & Provisioning State Machine

skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor<<connected>> #C8E6C9
  BackgroundColor<<disconnected>> #FFCDD2
  BackgroundColor<<provisioning>> #BBDEFB
  BackgroundColor<<testing>> #FFF9C4
}

state "WiFi OFF\n(Driver Not Started)" as OFF <<disconnected>>

state "STA Mode" as STA {
  state "Connecting..." as STA_CONN <<disconnected>>
  state "Connected\n(Got IP)" as STA_OK <<connected>>
  state "Retry Loop\n(max retries)" as STA_RETRY <<disconnected>>
  state "Failed\n(retries exhausted)" as STA_FAIL <<disconnected>>
}

state "AP+STA Mode\n(Provisioning Portal)" as PORTAL <<provisioning>> {
  state "Portal Active\nSSID: aqnode-[MAC]\nPass: setup123" as PORTAL_ACTIVE
  state "Captive DNS\nUDP :53 → 192.168.4.1" as CDNS
  state "HTTP Server\n:80 (21 handlers)" as HTTP

  PORTAL_ACTIVE --> CDNS
  PORTAL_ACTIVE --> HTTP
}

state "Testing Credentials" as TEST <<testing>> {
  state "Pre-scan\n(search SSID)" as PRESCAN
  state "Disconnect STA\n(keep AP alive)" as TEST_DISC
  state "Connect test\n(max 3 retries, 15s)" as TEST_CONN
  state "Restore previous\nSTA config" as TEST_RESTORE
}

' ── Boot transitions ──
[*] --> OFF : ESP32 power-on

OFF --> STA_CONN : Credentials\nfound in NVS
OFF --> PORTAL_ACTIVE : No credentials\nin NVS

' ── STA transitions ──
STA_CONN --> STA_OK : IP_EVENT_STA_GOT_IP\n→ Set CONNECTED_BIT\n→ Reset retry = 0
STA_CONN --> STA_RETRY : WIFI_EVENT_STA_DISCONNECTED

STA_RETRY --> STA_CONN : retry < MAX\n→ esp_wifi_connect()
STA_RETRY --> STA_FAIL : retry >= MAX\n→ Set FAIL_BIT

STA_OK --> STA_RETRY : WIFI_EVENT_STA_DISCONNECTED\n(connection lost)

' ── Portal transitions ──
STA_FAIL --> PORTAL_ACTIVE : Auto-open portal\n(s_provisioning_auto_opened)
STA_OK --> PORTAL_ACTIVE : User POST\n/api/provisioning/start

PORTAL_ACTIVE --> STA_CONN : User POST /api/provisioning/stop\n(has credentials, not connected)
PORTAL_ACTIVE --> STA_OK : User POST /api/provisioning/stop\n(already connected → STA only)

' ── Test-before-save flow ──
PORTAL_ACTIVE --> PRESCAN : User POST /wifi\n(new SSID + password)

PRESCAN --> TEST_DISC : SSID found\nin scan results
PRESCAN --> PORTAL_ACTIVE : SSID not found\n→ WIFI_TEST_RESULT_NOT_FOUND

TEST_DISC --> TEST_CONN : Apply test config\n→ esp_wifi_connect()

TEST_CONN --> STA_OK : Test SUCCESS\n→ Save to NVS\n→ WIFI_TEST_RESULT_CONNECTED
TEST_CONN --> TEST_RESTORE : Test FAILED\n(wrong password / timeout)

TEST_RESTORE --> PORTAL_ACTIVE : Restore AP+STA\n→ Return error to user
TEST_RESTORE --> STA_CONN : Not in portal mode\n→ Restore original STA

' ── Management actions ──
STA_OK --> STA_CONN : POST /api/wifi/disconnect\n→ Reconnects immediately \nvia event handler

STA_OK -[#red]-> OFF : POST /api/wifi/forget\n→ Erase NVS\n→ Delayed restart (2s)
PORTAL_ACTIVE -[#red]-> OFF : POST /api/wifi/forget\n→ Erase NVS\n→ Delayed restart (2s)

' ── Auto-reconnect probe ──
note right of STA_FAIL
  **Auto-reconnect probe:**
  When portal was auto-opened
  (s_provisioning_auto_opened),
  clock_sync_task periodically
  probes original STA credentials
  while in AP+STA mode.
  On success → switch to STA only.
end note

@enduml
